  "prompt": "How do we forget any Wi-Fi in Windows 10?",
  "response": "To forget a Wi-Fi network in Windows 10, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Network & Internet Settings:**\n   - Click on the Start button and then click on the \"Settings\" icon (the gear-shaped icon).\n   - In the Settings window, click on \"Network & Internet\".\n\n2. **Go to Wi-Fi Settings:**\n   - In the left sidebar, click on \"Wi-Fi\".\n\n3. **Manage Known Networks:**\n   - Scroll down and click on \"Manage known networks\".\n\n4. **Select the Network to Forget:**\n   - You will see a list of all the Wi-Fi networks your computer has connected to.\n   - Click on the network you want to forget.\n\n5. **Forget the Network:**\n   - Click on the \"Forget\" button.\n\nAfter completing these steps, your computer will no longer automatically connect to the selected Wi-Fi network, and you will need to enter the password again if you want to connect to it in the future.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or the network does not appear in the list, you may need to restart your computer or check your network adapter settings.",
